  [error] Invalid cast
   ╭─[test.lis:4:3]
 3 │   let b: byte = 65;
 4 │   b as string
   ·   ─────┬─────
   ·        ╰── cannot cast `byte` to `string`
 5 │ }
   ╰────
  help: A byte has two readings as a string. Use `[b] as string` to preserve the byte (may be invalid UTF-8), or cast through a rune to encode as a codepoint: `let r = b as rune; r as string` · code: [infer.invalid_cast]
